===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈkɒm.juˌnɪzm̩/|lang=en}}

===Etymology===
A calque of the {{etyl|de|en}} word {{m|de|Kommunismus}} (from Marx and Engels's ''[http://www.marxists.org/archive/marx/works/1848/communist-manifesto/index.htm Manifesto of the German Communist Party]''), in turn a calque of the {{etyl|fr|en}} word {{m|fr|communisme}}, which was formed from {{m|fr|commun||common}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|communis}}, and the suffix {{m|fr|-isme||-ism}}.

[[Image:Hammer and sickle.svg|thumb|right|120px|The [[red]] flag, particularly when marked with a [[yellow]] [[hammer]] intersecting a yellow [[sickle]], is an [[icon]]ic [[symbol]] of communism.]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# Any political philosophy or ideology advocating holding the production of resources collectively.
#* {{w|D. H. Lawrence}}
#*: I want to gather together about twenty souls and sail away from this world of war and squalor and found a little colony where there shall be no money but a sort of '''communism''' as far as necessaries of life go, and some real decency.
# Any political social system that implements a communist political philosophy.
# The international socialist society where classes and the state no longer exist.

